With the definition of 1 in the context, 1 + 1 is <code>g1&larr;c2 c1, ((fix v1 v2. v3. case v2 { c1. v3 | c2. v4. (c2 ((v1 v4) v3)) }) g1) g1</code>.
Reducing this term gives <code>g1&larr;c2 c1, c2 (c2 c1)</code>, that is 2, as shown in the reduction example above.
This concludes to proof.
</p>
